# Pinned upstream registry refs the publisher compiles from, sourced by
# scripts/publish.sh. Renovate owns freshness: the repo-local customManager
# in renovate.json bumps each tag+commit pair (the fleet's Dockerfile
# `digest=commit` convention adapted to this env file), the PR automerges
# through the validate gate, and the merge fires publish.yaml's push
# trigger — so a release follows every upstream registry update at the
# Renovate sweep cadence instead of waiting for the daily cron.
#
# The COMMIT is the tag's dereferenced commit: publish.sh fetches codeload
# tarballs BY COMMIT, so git content addressing is the integrity anchor
# and a moved upstream tag shows up as a digest-only Renovate PR.
#
# renovate: datasource=github-tags depName=jdx/mise digest=commit
MISE_REF=v2026.7.12
MISE_COMMIT=f98d8cba039878938ffff0bbd5b6070501fd432a
# renovate: datasource=github-tags depName=aquaproj/aqua-registry digest=commit
AQUA_REF=v4.542.0
AQUA_COMMIT=de217ddf7ba673eddb9cf5d0689a7f3e0a07c84e
